We had her for the first half of A67, she was good with proofs and would spend time explaining them to you if you didn't understand something. She was also available outside of class although her office hours sometimes got really busy. She was nice and I would take her class again.

The lectures are nothing compared to hw, she simply does not care about the students at all and uses the course to weed out incoming students from CS post. Work hard, spend hours figuring out the material from other sources and you will pull through. Do not depend on her being fair or helpful at all. The ta's are paid to not give a damn about you.
